Client Services



Wight Martindale
				Executive Vice President, Director of Business Development


				  Wight Martindale joined Solus in March 2012 as an Executive Vice President. Wight leads our new business development efforts and dedicates most of his time to working with existing and prospective clients. Wight has more than 20 years of experience in leveraged finance - 14 years at Deutsche Bank/Bankers Trust (1994-2009), including Head of High Yield and Distressed Debt Sales from 2005 to 2009, and the same role at RBS from 2009 to 2012. Wight has worked closely with some of the largest institutional clients in High Yield and Distressed Debt. He began his career at PaineWebber in 1987. Wight received a BA from Lehigh University and is on the Board of Trustees of The Peddie School.
				



Filipa Fink
				Managing Director, Business Development & Investor Relations


				  Mrs. Fink joined Solus in March 2014 as a Managing Director in the Business Development & Investor Relations group, where she focuses on capital raising and relationship development with both existing and prospective clients. Prior to joining Solus, Filipa worked at Och-Ziff Capital Management Group in the Investor Relations team in London and New York. Before Och-Ziff, Mrs. Fink was at UBS AG in the New York and Zurich offices. Mrs. Fink received a Masters of Science in Economics and Management from HEC. She received a Bachelor of Arts from the University of Pennsylvania.
				



Christie Kinney
				Managing Director, Director of Client Services


				  Ms. Kinney joined Solus in July 2007 as a Vice President in its Investor Relations group. She has been working with the Firm's funds since she joined Stanfield Capital Partners in 2003. Prior to joining Stanfield, Ms. Kinney was the Head of Marketing for Non-Proprietary Retail Distribution of the firm's mutual funds at Merrill Lynch Investment Managers ("Merrill") from 2000 to 2003. Prior to Merrill, Ms. Kinney was with Bankers Trust where she was responsible for the sales and marketing of mutual funds to institutions and financial professionals. Ms. Kinney began her career in 1989 with Jennison Associates in portfolio accounting. She received a Bachelor of Science in Business with a Marketing concentration from Marist College.
				



Samantha Lowe
				Managing Director, Business Development & Investor Relations


				  Mrs. Lowe joined Solus in February 2014. She is a Managing Director in the Business Development & Investor Relations group, where she focuses on capital raising and relationship development with both existing and prospective clients. Prior to joining Solus, Mrs. Lowe worked at Silver Point Capital in the Marketing and Investor Relations group. Before Silver Point, Mrs. Lowe was an analyst at Bank of America Merrill Lynch for three years where she focused on credit related transactions within the Global Corporate and Investment Bank. Mrs. Lowe attended the Olin School of Business at Washington University in St. Louis where she received a Bachelor of Science in Business Administration with majors in Finance and Marketing.
				



Michael Trefz, CFA
				Managing Director, Business Development & Investor Relations


				  Mr. Trefz joined Solus in July 2015 as a Managing Director in the Business Development & Investor Relations group. Prior to joining Solus, Mr. Trefz had been with Brevan Howard since 2012, where he was a Marketer for ten of the firm's hedge fund strategies and a Product Specialist for the special opportunity BH Argentina Fund. Prior to that he was a Director in the Institutional Sales Group at Wedge Alternatives, raising capital for hedge funds, private equity, infrastructure funds, as well as for direct/co-investments in private companies. He started his career as a fixed income derivatives analyst with GE Asset Management. Mike graduated cum laude with a Bachelor of Science in Finance from the University of Connecticut and is a Chartered Financial Analyst.
				



Hallie Finan
				Director, Business Development & Investor Relations


				  Ms. Finan joined Solus in September 2012. She is a Director in the Business Development & Investor Relations group. Ms. Finan focuses on capital raising and relationship development with existing and prospective clients. Additionally, Ms. Finan assists in operational and investment due diligence conducted by current and potential clients. Prior to joining Solus, Ms. Finan worked as a Markets Analyst in the credit, rates and MBS/ABS groups within the fixed income sales and trading division at the Royal Bank of Scotland. Ms. Finan attended Trinity College where she received a Bachelor of Science in Economics.
				



Lori Fishman
				Director, Client Services


				  Mrs. Fishman joined Solus in August 2007 as an Associate in its Investor Relations group. She has been working with the Firm's Investor Relations/Client Services team since she joined Stanfield Capital Partners in 2003. Prior to joining Stanfield, Mrs. Fishman worked at OFFITBANK in their Marketing/Client Services department. She received a Bachelor of Arts from the University of Kentucky. 
				



Ulana Blahy
				Assistant Vice President, Client Services


				  Ms. Blahy joined Solus in January 2014 as an Associate in the Client Services group. Prior to joining Solus, Ulana worked at Indus Capital Partners in the Marketing and Investor Relations group. Prior to Indus, Ulana was with Edelman Public Relations. She received a Bachelor of Arts in Communications & Media Studies from Fordham University and a MBA from Fordham University Graduate School of Business. 
				






